1 E. Subject to the availability of funding, the Commission shall
2 review the report responses submitted pursuant to subsection D of
3 this section and select one approved applicant teacher education
4 program to receive Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($500,000.00) to
5 enact the initiatives outlined in the program’s report response.
6 F. By December 31, 2027, the Commission shall electronically
7 submit a report of TeachForwardOK’s findings and recommendations to
8 the Governor, the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, and the
9 Speaker of the House of Representatives.
10 G. The Commission shall promulgate rules to implement the
11 provisions of this section.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
13 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
14 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
15 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
16 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
